{"type":"assistant.message","data":{"messageId":"e78dd5d0-ef31-42c1-966d-1f91a9874c98","content":"You already have the HotReload extension referenced. To use it, run your tests with `dotnet test` in **watch mode**:\n\n```bash\ndotnet watch test --project TestProject.csproj\n```\n\nThis leverages `Microsoft.Testing.Extensions.HotReload` to re-run tests automatically whenever you save a file change — no need to manually rebuild or re-run.\n\n**Workflow:**\n1. Start `dotnet watch test` in one terminal.\n2. Edit your test or source files to fix failures.\n3. On save, tests re-run automatically with hot reload (no full rebuild).\n\nThis gives you a tight feedback loop for iterating on fixes.","toolRequests":[],"interactionId":"873f5095-84db-46d5-9f50-307749b02ad0","outputTokens":152,"requestId":"EC47:B0316:33CEB6B:393D3A5:6A02FA4C"},"id":"5e149a4c-370f-4768-8260-dccb60cc089c","timestamp":"2026-05-12T10:00:55.367Z","parentId":"a2a275f4-bb77-4b1f-98b3-be49400ec23d"}
